.TH "gfs2_glock_async_wait" 9 "gfs2_glock_async_wait" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
gfs2_glock_async_wait \- wait on multiple asynchronous glock acquisitions
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" gfs2_glock_async_wait
.BI "(unsigned int num_gh "  ","
.BI "struct gfs2_holder *ghs "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "num_gh" 12
the number of holders in the array
.IP "ghs" 12
the glock holder array
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success, meaning all glocks have been granted and are held.
-ESTALE if the request timed out, meaning all glocks were released,
and the caller should retry the operation.
